  <subsection>
            <title>Algorithms with Pseudocode and Flowcharts</title>
            <p>For complex problems, it is important to plan your solution before writing code. <term>Pseudocode</term> is a simplified, informal way of describing the steps in an algorithm in a human language like English but following the sequence, selection, and repetition structure of a programming language.  <term>Flowcharts</term> are diagrams that represent the steps in an algorithm like below. Selection is usually represented as a triangle in a flowchart, and arrows are used to show repetition. Both pseudocode and flowcharts are tools that help you plan your algorithm before writing code.</p>
